acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

addVault(address).details: adds a vault to the total balance

getNumaSupply().details: total numa supply without wallet's list balances

getTotalBalanceEth().details: sum of all vaults balances in Eth

getTotalBalanceEthNoDebt().details: sum of all vaults balances in Eth excluding debts

numaToToken(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint.details: How many lst tokens from numa amount

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

removeVault(address).details: removes a vault from total balance

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBuyFee(uint16).details: Set Buy fee percentage (exemple: 5% fee --> fee = 950)

setNuAssetManager(address).details: set the INuAssetManager address (used to compute synth value in Eth)

setSellFee(uint16).details: Set Sell fee percentage (exemple: 5% fee --> fee = 950)

tokenToNuma(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint.details: How many Numas from lst token amount

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

getNumaSupply().notice: for another vault, either we use this function from this vault, either we need to set list in the other vault too

lockSupplyFlashloan(bool).notice: lock numa supply in case of a flashloan so that numa price does not change
